name: Collection health
label: Collection health
description: Code lists for collection health indicators adopted from Favret and others, 2008, http://favret.aphidnet.org/pubs/Favret_et-al_2008b.pdf

terms.name: Level_1
terms.description: Mixed taxa stored in the same vial, jar, unit tray, slide, etc. Annelid slides made from same collection are in different boxes.

terms.name: Level_2
terms.description: Specimens crowded. Species sharing trays, or taxa scattered in two or more places. Arrangement is only at a higher taxonomic level. More than one annelid sample for collection site is stored in the same box.

terms.name: Level_3
terms.description: Specimens arranged alphabetically by family, genus, and species, or, if arranged phylogenetically, with an alphabetical cross-referenced list. Annelid slides arranged in boxes according to collection event and/or locality.

terms.name: Level_4
terms.description: Specimens arranged geographically within a taxon, or arranged numerically by catalog number if specimens have been databased.

terms.name: Level_1
terms.description: Level 1 is not defined.

terms.name: Level_2
terms.description: No computerization at all.

terms.name: Level_3
terms.description: All [herbarium, mollusk, and vertebrate] specimens databased. Taxonomic information of other groups electronically inventoried, but specimens themselves not yet databased and assigned catalog numbers.

terms.name: Level_4
terms.description: All localities geo-referenced and stored electronically. Invertebrates databased at the level of storage unit (pin, vial, jar, slide).

terms.name: Level_1
terms.description: Labels are faded to illegible, crumbling, or missing. Labels have become detached from the specimen.

terms.name: Level_2
terms.description: Labels are partially faded, laser-printed in fluid or in pencil, or on non-archival paper

terms.name: Level_3
terms.description: Labels are readily legible, printed with non-bleeding (if in fluid) archival paper and ink.

terms.name: Level_1
terms.description: Shells have Byne’s disease. Specimens (of any kind) have signs of pest infestation. Insect specimens have fallen off of pin. Specimens are damaged to the point of being unusable

terms.name: Level_2
terms.description: Specimens are damaged: broken into multiple pieces, with past pest damage, loose teeth or bones. Insect pins are broken or significantly bent.

terms.name: Level_3
terms.description: All specimens are intact and stable.

terms.name: Level_1
terms.description: Specimens are desiccated. Fluid does not completely cover specimen(s). Alcohol is opaque.

terms.name: Level_2
terms.description: Fluid level is low, but completely covers specimens. Alcohol is dark

terms.name: Level_3
terms.description: Fluid is topped-off and relatively clear

terms.name: Level_1
terms.description: Slide or cover slip is broken. Mounting medium is crystallized, running, or has receded up to specimen.

terms.name: Level_2
terms.description: Aqueous mounting medium is not sealed (ringed) under cover slip. Mounting medium has receded. Cover slip or slide is cracked.

terms.name: Level_3
terms.description: Slide in good condition. Mounted in Canada balsam or cover slip has been sealed (ringed).

terms.name: Level_1
terms.description: Specimens in old cardboard boxes, cigar boxes, pill boxes, or paper bags. Specimens not stored in unit trays. Plants mounted on cardboard with rubber cement

terms.name: Level_2
terms.description: Specimens stored in new cardboard boxes or zip-lock bags. Vertebrate trays are unlined. Skulls or skeletal material are in substandard containers. Insects pinned in hard-bottom unit trays. Plants pressed in newspaper. Fungi kept in packets when they should be in boxes, or glued to paper in the packets.

terms.name: Level_3
terms.description: Unit trays are archival. Insects pinned in foam-bottom trays. Vertebrate trays are lined with acid-free paper. Plants and fungi are in/on acid paper/packet/box withElmer’s or other non-archival glue, or lacking fragment folders.

terms.name: Level_4
terms.description: Plants and fungi in/on acid free paper/packet/box, fixed with acid free glue, and with fragment folders present.

terms.name: Level_1
terms.description: Vial stoppers are cracked, broken, swollen, or disintegrating. Stoppers are made of cork. Vials are loose on shelf, or banded together, and not in vial rack. Jar lids are old and rusted (if metal), or are BakeliteH lids (which crack easily). Jar seals are missing, cracked, or shrinking. Five-gallon buckets have poor seals or loose lids.

terms.name: Level_2
terms.description: Hardened but intact vial stoppers. Vials aligned in wire-sided racks. Jar lids are metal or with non-polyethylene jar seals. Large specimens are stored in 5-gallon buckets.

terms.name: Level_3
terms.description: Vials have good quality stoppers. Vial racks are solid with no risk of vial loss. Jars are bail-topped with polyethylene gaskets, or have polypropylene lids. Large specimens are stored in archival barrels with clamping sealing mechanisms.

terms.name: Level_1
terms.description: Slides not in slide box or tray. Slide box broken.

terms.name: Level_2
terms.description: Slide box not standard 100-slide box. Slides in trays are not protected by envelope or thick labels, which prevent the crushing of the cover slip on one slide by the adjoining slide.

terms.name: Level_3
terms.description: Good slide boxes or trays with rust-free hinges and substantial closure clasps.

terms.name: Level_4
terms.description: Tray slides stored flat.

terms.name: Level_1
terms.description: Data are in codes or missing entirely.

terms.name: Level_2
terms.description: Some data are missing but can be inferred. Specimen containers (vials, jars, or slides) lack determination labels.

terms.name: Level_3
terms.description: All data fields are complete for all groups except pinned insects may have determination labels missing.

terms.name: Level_4
terms.description: Localities fully geo-referenced. All species-level insect pins have determination labels.

name: nggdpp_collection_types
label: NGGDPP Collection Types
description: Terms denoting the type/function of collection items in the National Digital Catalog

terms.name: ndc_collection
terms.label: NDC Collection
terms.description: Item that represents a logical collection of physical data items managed by an organization contributing to the National Digital Catalog. These are core metadata items for which we expect to find full metadata describing the collection and a method of accessing the contents in the collection.

terms.name: ndc_folder
terms.label: NDC Folder
terms.description: Denotes a ScienceBase Item that functions as an organizational folder within the National Digital Catalog.

terms.name: ndc_organization
terms.label: NDC Organization
terms.description: Item that represents a contributing organization. Used to set permissions in ScienceBase to allow management access by members of the organization.
